    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Corbin Carroll** leads the charge with an elite 87.14 efficiency rating. He sits in a perfect storm of positive indicators: batting second against a favorable right-handed arm in Walker, with an impressive 0.372 xwOBA anchoring his projection. The high-upside play of the day belongs to **Mickey Moniak**, who jumps to a 75.75 rating thanks to a massive 14% boost from a dynamic platoon edge and a favorable matchup against M\u00e1rquez, whose slow delivery (86% SB rate allowed) provides a significant secondary boost to his stolen base potential. Similarly, **Vinnie Pasquantino** takes full advantage of the high-ERA Fedde matchup, clearing the 75-point threshold as his order and platoon splits align to maximize run-production potential.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Trevor Story**, who sits at a 49.25 efficiency. Despite a decent base projection, the matchup against Leahy\u2014who carries a respectable 3.73 xERA\u2014coupled with a park penalty, ultimately pushed him below the threshold compared to our starting middle infielders. Our lineup remains heavily weighted toward hitters with favorable platoon splits against right-handed starters; the contrast is evident in our treatment of **Jose Caballero**, whose -13% platoon penalty when facing Martinez effectively neutralized the raw value of his profile, forcing him into a reserve role. \n\nWhile we are optimized for today, owners should keep an eye on **James Wood**; he is our only starter facing a southpaw today, and his 62.66 rating is largely tethered to his leadoff spot. Should late weather patterns shift or lineup cards reveal unexpected defensive adjustments, we are prepared to pivot to the high-floor depth of **Austin Riley** or **Zach McKinstry** to maintain our competitive edge in the 5x5 landscape. Be mindful that while **Max Muncy** and **Kyle Karros** are active, their scores sit near our 50-point marginal floor\u2014they are clear targets for substitution if mid-game news breaks regarding pitching changes.",
